SWINE FEVER/HOG CHOLERA - SPAIN (02)
=====================================
[see
Swine fever/Hog cholera - Spain 970426150528]
Date: Sat, 03 May 1997 11:12:50 -0300
From: Dorothy Preslar <dpreslar@fas.org>
Subject: May 2 OIE Reports
CLASSICAL SWINE FEVER IN SPAIN
See also: 25 April 1997
Follow-up report No. 1
Translation of a fax received on 25 April 1997 from Dr J. Nombela Maqueda,
Deputy Director General of Animal Health, Ministry of Agriculture, Fisheries
and Food, Madrid:
End of previous report period: 18 April 1997 (see Disease Information, 10
[17], 63).
End of this report period: 24 April 1997.
New outbreaks:
Location Lerida province, Catalonia Autonomous Community
No. of outbreaks 8
Total number of outbreaks identified since 1 January 1997: ten (10).
Total number of animals in the new outbreaks:
susceptible 10,596 *
cases 2,734
deaths 577
destroyed 10,019
slaughtered 0
* 8,474 fattening pigs, 478 breeding pigs and 1,644 piglets.
Diagnosis:
A. Laboratory where diagnosis was made: Animal Production and Health
Laboratory, Algete (Madrid).
B. Diagnostic tests used: direct immunofluorescence and ELISA.
Epidemiology:
A. Source of agent / origin of infection: these are secondary outbreaks.
B. Mode of spread: investigations under way.
C. Other epidemiological details: these new outbreaks occurred in the same
districts as the first two registered outbreaks: Bell Lloch d'Urgel and
Torregrosa.
Control measures during reporting period: stamping out; ban on movement in
the vicinity of the affected farms; protection and surveillance zones;
epidemiological investigations under way.
---
